Mitsubishi UFJ Will Gain 22.4% of Morgan Stanley in Preferred Conversion

-- B y   S t e v e n   F r o m m
-- 
2011-04-21T13:18:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-21/mitsubishi-ufj-will-gain-22-4-of-morgan-stanley-in-preferred-conversion.html
Mitsubishi UFJ Financial Group Inc. (8306) 
and  Morgan Stanley (MS)  said they have entered into an agreement to
convert MUFGâ€™s outstanding convertible preferred stock in Morgan
Stanley into Morgan Stanley common stock.   Mitsubishi UFJ will exchange convertible preferred stock
with a face value of $7.8 billion and a 10 percent dividend for
385 million shares of Morgan Stanley common stock, an increase
in the conversion rate of 75 million shares and providing
Mitsubishi UFJ with an ownership interest in Morgan Stanley of
22.4 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
